The paper discusses the use of machine learning models, specifically recurrent neural networks, to predict future resource usage and detect anomalies in computer systems. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of telemetry data to train the models, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of this model into existing applications without requiring changes, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of this model for tasks such as predicting future resource usage, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
